<figure class="diagram">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 680 260" role="img" aria-labelledby="lf-title lf-desc" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
    <title id="lf-title">Why localhost cost 10 seconds</title>
    <desc id="lf-desc">
      The app connects to localhost. Windows tries IPv6 first: nothing listens on ::1, and
      without a timeout the client waits 10,137 milliseconds before the OS falls back to
      IPv4, where Docker answers in 27 milliseconds. Connecting to 127.0.0.1 directly skips
      the dead end.
    </desc>
    <defs>
      <marker id="lf-arrow" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto-start-reverse">
        <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="var(--dim)" />
      </marker>
    </defs>
    <rect x="230" y="16" width="220" height="48" rx="4" fill="none" stroke="var(--line)" />
    <text x="340" y="37" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--fg)" font-size="14" font-weight="700">app connects to</text>
    <text x="340" y="55" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--accent)" font-size="14" font-weight="700">localhost:5433</text>

    <path d="M 300 64 L 195 108" fill="none" stroke="var(--dim)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#lf-arrow)" />
    <text x="215" y="82" text-anchor="end" fill="var(--dim)" font-size="12">windows tries IPv6 first</text>

    <rect x="60" y="112" width="270" height="64" rx="4" fill="none" stroke="var(--accent)" />
    <text x="195" y="136" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--fg)" font-size="14" font-weight="700">::1 — nothing listening</text>
    <text x="195" y="156" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--accent)" font-size="13">no timeout set · waits 10,137 ms</text>

    <path d="M 330 144 L 361 144" fill="none" stroke="var(--dim)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#lf-arrow)" />

    <rect x="365" y="112" width="240" height="64" rx="4" fill="none" stroke="var(--ok)" />
    <text x="485" y="136" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--fg)" font-size="14" font-weight="700">127.0.0.1 — Docker answers</text>
    <text x="485" y="156" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--ok)" font-size="13">connects in 27 ms</text>

    <path d="M 450 40 H 640 V 216 H 625" fill="none" stroke="var(--ok)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4 4" marker-end="url(#lf-arrow)" />
    <rect x="353" y="196" width="268" height="40" rx="4" fill="none" stroke="var(--line)" />
    <text x="487" y="221" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--fg)" font-size="13">fix: connect to <tspan fill="var(--ok)" font-weight="700">127.0.0.1</tspan> directly</text>
  </svg>
  <figcaption class="meta">
    One word decides the route: localhost knocks on the dead IPv6 door first; 127.0.0.1 walks straight in.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

